@data_filter @robertwiblin @fchollet My definition of AGI:

AI that's powerful enough that if one day all humans suddenly disappear and the AI is uploaded into robot bodies, it would be able to independently continue civilization.

That requires a high level of capability and a very high level of generality.

@GiulioRebuffo @fede_intern I'd say high bandwidth is a more dangerous assumption to make than high compute reqs. The basic reason is if you have a computer you (generally) can expect to keep that computer, but an internet connection has no such guarantees. Reasons:

* censorship
* disruption to internet

